00:05:17.170 --> 00:05:20.420
Let’s just start by defining what “fungible” means.

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:25.610
It means interchangeable, that it can be equally changed for something else.

00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:30.490
A 10 euro note is fungible, it can be changed for

00:05:30.490 --> 00:05:34.000
another 10 euro note, they have exactly the same value.

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:36.190
A bitcoin is fungible.

00:05:36.370 --> 00:05:42.150
One bitcoin is the same as another bitcoin, they also have exactly the same value.

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:46.710
A painting, on the other hand, is non-fungible.

00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:53.110
Each one is slightly different, and there are no two that are exactly the same.

00:05:54.290 --> 00:06:00.734
So, if something is a non-fungible token, it is a unique digital asset.

00:06:00.957 --> 00:06:06.690
It could be a picture of a rock, it could be a certificate, it could be linked

00:06:06.750 --> 00:06:11.660
to something that actually exists in the physical world, like a house or a car.

00:06:13.020 --> 00:06:19.150
The idea is that it is a secure way of proving ownership of something, and

00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:24.130
defining certain rules for what should happen to that thing in the future.

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:29.000
It all works on something called the blockchain, which is a subject for

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:35.030
another day, but in essence creates a secure way for ownership of anything,

00:06:35.350 --> 00:06:40.880
both digital and non-digital, to be transferred from one party to another.

00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:43.100
This is called a smart contract.

